fields.name: Northern Pine Exhibit
fields.description: Grand exhibit that hosts our bears and moose

fields.name: Northern Water Exhibit
fields.description: The Northern Water Exhibit houses our aquatic animals with the likes of alligators, otters, and tortoises.

fields.name: Central Jungle Exhibit
fields.description: The Central Jungle Exhibit holds our primate family with the likes of Chimps, Gorillas, and Orangutans.

fields.name: Western Jungle Exhibit
fields.description: The Western Jungle Exhibit is home to our cute yet dangerous tigers.

fields.name: Southern Swamp Exhibit
fields.description: The Southern Swamp Exhibit is home to our hippos.

fields.name: Southern Grass land Exhibit
fields.description: The Southern Grass land Exhibit is home to our Horses, Deer, and Bison.

fields.name: Southern Outback Exhibit
fields.description: The Southern Outback Exhibit is home to our Kangaroos, Rhinos, and Emus.

fields.name: Eastern Reptile Exhibit
fields.description: Our Eastern Reptile Exhibit is home to our Snakes, Turtles, and Frogs.

fields.name: Eastern Arctic Exhibit
fields.description: Our Eastern Arctic Exhibit is home to our cute and fluffy Penguin family.

fields.name: Eastern Arial Exhibit
fields.description: Our Eastern Arial Exhibit is home to our bird family with the likes of Eagles, Herons, and Flamingos.

fields.name: Pulmonary arterial hypertension
fields.description: A type of high blood pressure that affects arteries in the lungs and in the heart.

fields.name: Rabies
fields.description: A viral zoonotic disease that causes progressive and fatal inflammation of the brain and spinal cord.

fields.name: Avian pox
fields.description: Wart-like growths on the skin, particularly on unfeathered parts of the body such as the legs, feet, eyelids, base of the beak, and the comb and wattles.

fields.name: Influenza
fields.description: A contagious respiratory illness caused by influenza viruses that infect the nose, throat, and sometimes the lungs.

fields.name: Salmonella
fields.description: A common bacterial disease that affects the intestinal tract.

fields.name: Lumpy skin disease
fields.description: A viral disease that affects cattle.

fields.name: Ursa
fields.description: Ursa is the mother of two cubs. She is a single mom that is working hard to provide for her kids.

fields.name: Ellie
fields.description: Ellie is one of two twins and is super playful and loves attention

fields.name: Eli
fields.description: Eli Is one of two twins and is quite reserved and enjoys his alone time

fields.name: Buck
fields.description: Buck is an old moose and rarely is seen without his best bud Chuck.

fields.name: Chuck
fields.description: Chuck is an old moose and rarely is seen without his best bud Buck.

fields.name: Mac
fields.description: Mac is a lucky otter that was born with only one eye but has been able to survive and is a new years baby.

fields.name: Rocko
fields.description: Rocko is a extremely fat otter who loves to do tricks for guests that give him food.

fields.name: Phil
fields.description: Phil loves to hangout in the sun and enjoys spending more time out of water then in it.

fields.name: Randolf
fields.description: Randolf is one of our extremely sociable alligators who loves shiny items that guest will bring and show.

fields.name: Kelly
fields.description: Kelly is our biggest pound for pound alligator our zoo has ever had and is a staggering 17 feet long. She however brings in many guests due to her massive size.

fields.name: Premi
fields.description: Premi is our baby chimp who love to play with new toys that we buy.

fields.name: Silver
fields.description: Silver is our Silver Back gorilla and has taken leadership of the primates, he is also very slow to anger and makes a great leader.

fields.name: Bolo
fields.description: Bolo is our oldest animal here at the zoo and is a very wise primate who will be seen to use tools such as saws and hammers when we give them to him.

fields.name: Mango
fields.description: Mango is the mother of Premi and is a very reserved chimp who follow Silvers lead while mothering her baby.

fields.name: Stripes
fields.description: Stripes is one of our great tigers and loves nothing more than a good back scratch... and live prey.

fields.name: Pickles
fields.description: Pickles is our tiger who is the mate of Stripes and basically follows her lead.

fields.name: Rambo
fields.description: Rambo is our heaviest animal in the zoo weighting in at a staggering 834 pounds but still looks great for his weight.

fields.name: Mark
fields.description: Mark is one of our bison and is often seen sitting in the corner of his exhibit enjoying the shade.

fields.name: Ello
fields.description: Ello is one of our bison who is super sociable and is often seen close up to guests... watch out for his tounge!

fields.name: Rapper
fields.description: Rapper is our horse and one of the main attractions at the zoo. Guests can come and take ride on rapper who enjoys going on runs with guests.

fields.name: Nami
fields.description: Nami is one of our deer who enjoys hanging out with her two brothers Botsa and Chile.

fields.name: Botsa
fields.description: Botsa is one of our deer who is constantly annoyed at nami but will often be seen watching out for her when she is eating or sleeping.

fields.name: Chile
fields.description: Chile is one of our deer and he is just there, nothing much going on in this ones head.

fields.name: Kicker
fields.description: Kicker is one of our Kangaroos and is often seen play fighting with his brother Sudan.

fields.name: Sudan
fields.description: Sudan is one of our Kangaroos and is often seen play fighting with his brother Kicker.

fields.name: Rhinosaur
fields.description: Rhinosaur is one of our famous animals at the zoo. We were asked to take him in after he had flipped a car full of poachers taking all of them out in South Sudan.

fields.name: Ekans
fields.description: Ekans is one of our many emus and is often seen running around his exhibit to let out all his energy

fields.name: Ali
fields.description: Ali is one of our many emus and is often seen running beside Ekans trying to calm him down.

fields.name: Risiki
fields.description: Risiki is one of our many emus and is often seen hanging out with our rhino.

fields.name: Slither
fields.description: Slither is one of our snakes and has the most venoms bite in the entire zoo. A human would last 15 min before exploding after a bite from slither.

fields.name: Skal
fields.description: Skal is one of our snakes and is often seen hanging out in his toy pineapple house.

fields.name: Bubbles
fields.description: Bubbles is one of our Turtles and is seen often creating bubbles in his tank.

fields.name: Jupiter
fields.description: Jupiter is one of our frogs who is very energetic and often jumping onto different rocks in his cage.

fields.name: Marcus
fields.description: Marcus is one of our frogs who is often seen upside down hanging onto the roof of his enclosure.

fields.name: Milly
fields.description: Milly is One of our penguins who is often seen collecting rocks and sorting them by size.

fields.name: Jill
fields.description: Jill is one of our penguins who loves to eat macaroni mor than anything in the world.

fields.name: Ember
fields.description: Ember is our Eagle and the most popular of our bird family. Her wingspan is a staggering 12 feet long.

fields.name: Blue
fields.description: Blue is one of our herons and gets his name by the navy blue feathers that fill his back up.

fields.name: Purple
fields.description: Purple is one of our herons and gets his name from his favorite color which is purple and is often seen interacting with guest who wear it.

fields.name: Pinky
fields.description: Pinky is one of our flamingos and is just pink.
